<item>
            <title>[LANG-1757] NullPointerException in MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1757</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello devs,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Calling MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod with the arguments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&#160;cls is the class of `java.nio.file.Files`&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;methodName is the string `exists`&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;parameterTypes is an array with the class of `java.nio.file.Path`&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;triggers a NullPointerException:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Cannot invoke &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt;.getName()&quot;&lt;/span&gt; because the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; value of &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt;.getSuperclass()&quot;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
&#160; &#160; at org.apache.commons.lang3.reflect.MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod(MethodUtils.java:354)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect it is this line: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-lang/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/lang3/reflect/MethodUtils.java#L352&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-lang/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/lang3/reflect/MethodUtils.java#L352&lt;/a&gt; that is buggy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In particular, I suspect the problem is that `java.nio.file.Path` is an interface which lacks a super class. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am happy to provide more information if needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for making this library. It has been very useful to us.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
